About us
Imagine. A traditional and cozy neighborhood pub. Many different types of beer. Lobster rolls. New England Clam Chowder. A Green Monster scoreboard. Jukebox music plays in the background. A crowd of Red Sox fans cheer on the team. Live music plays through, almost daily. Now imagine this entire scene readily available at a convenient location on Tamiami Trail in sunny Bonita Springs.
Sounds impossible, right?
Come visit us at Lansdowne Street in Bonita Springs and experience it for yourself.
The brick and rich, dark wood interior takes you a thousand miles from Florida as soon as you enter. A veritable museum of Red Sox memorabilia adorns the walls. An endless variety of microbrews and comfort beers hold their own against a wine list forty bottles strong.
Gourmet sandwiches rule the menu. Hearty soups and bountiful, crisp salads are perfect teammates to the Panini and baked brie. We only use fresh ingredients of the highest quality to craft our food. Here at Lansdowne Street you can indulge in authentic New England cuisine in a setting that looks and feels like a Boston pub without ever leaving Bonita Springs.
Lansdowne Street is the only restaurant and bar in Bonita Springs specializing in New England Sports. We've got plenty of televisions and show all the Red Sox, Patriots and Celtics games as they happen. Watch the games the way they do in Boston…with a Fenway-style crowd of like-minded fans cheering on the team.
